The Chalet le Heron is very well located, between the Tracadie River and the Grande Mer!
On foot and in a matter of minutes, you have access to a vast beach where you can bathe, relax on the sand or even fish for striped bass. For early risers, you can admire exceptional sunrises!

Friendly by nature, the Acadian Peninsula is full of beauties that are all accessible shortly. Whether you want to visit Miscou, its historic lighthouse and enjoy a meal at the Terrace in Steve with the two feet literally in the sand, visit the Aquarium and Shippagan Marin Center or the Acadian Historical Village of Caraquet, have a great coffee in a great cafe, or a beer in a microbrewery you will be served as desired!

For bike lovers!
The Route de la Peninsula Acadienne alone will charm you and will make you want to come back years after years. There are nearly 300 km of roadside trails including 80 km of closed asphalt circuit trails ( no motor traffic) which are of very high quality and very safe. name: Big and spacious Cabin overlooking the river
description: This cedar nature lodge overlooking the picturesque views of the Little Southwest Miramichi River. Step inside this spacious haven, once a meeting room transformed into a spacious cabin retreat. With two bedrooms, two bathrooms, and a fully-equipped kitchen, you'll have all the space you need for a memorable stay. A private hot tub is waiting for you. Soak up the tranquility, unwind in nature's embrace, and let the stresses of everyday life melt away.
neighborhood_overview: Surrounding the Lo'gsi'gan-The Cabin, you'll find the Miramichi River which is famous for fishing, swimming and tubing. Explore the area on foot through light, moderate and heavily trafficked walking trails. On the grounds you will find Metepenagiag Heritage Park, a modern interpretive center highlighting the 3000 year history of Metepenagiag's Mi'kmaq Culture.  Our trails lead to the river where you can go swimming, snorkeling or fishing.
host_about: Embracing the beauty of nature, heritage, and community. I am the General Manager of a lodge and cultural center nestled in breathtaking surroundings. Proudly showcasing indigenous history and creating unforgettable experiences. Grateful for the privilege to share my culture and celebrate the wonders of our land. Join myself and my amazing staff on this incredible journey!

As a successful host, I am looking to provide the best possible experience for guests visiting the city. There is nothing more reassuring and calming than finding a place that feels like a second home on your travels. 
To escape everyday life's tempo, I like going to the gym, am very interested in personal development, goal setting, real estate, investing, and playing sports.

name: The Shipbuilder's Cottage-Two Century Old Charm
description: Surrounded by spacious grounds, The Shipbuilder’s Cottage is one of two separate adjacent rental units (the Summer Kitchen). Built  in 1812 by shipbuilder Caleb Ward, the cottage is the oldest home in St. Martins. Its centrepiece is the original brick hearth around which many generations have enjoyed a meal, a pint and a fire on a chilly night. A well-equipped kitchen, an old oak dining table and a large sectional couch are arranged in a spacious room where the whole family can eat and relax.
neighborhood_overview: The cottage is located at 170 West Quaco Rd., 5 km from the Village of St. Martins, the harbour, restaurants, cafe, grocery, gas, art and gift shops, tourist information centre, museum and the Sea Caves. The Fundy Trail is 11 km from the village. Within walking distance of the cottage is The Quaco Head Lighthouse (1.3kms), and Brown's beach (1.9kms) - which is as quiet as it is scenic and a rock lover's dream. There is also a coastal trail that connects the two. On calm nights the world's highest tides can be heard washing into shore, carving the red rock coastline to smooth perfection.

name: Bay Watch Cottage,  on the Bay of Fundy
description:
Amazing location on a quiet road, on the Bay of Fundy. Relax, unwind and be present Enjoy the true east coast slow living vibe and leave the world behind. Bay Watch cottage is a cozy, century home, in south western New Brunswick.
Perfect for families, couples and weekend getaways.
Walking to nearby beach to search for sea glass, sand dollars, hermit crabs.
*Saint John 30 mins
*St. Andrews 40 mins
*New River Beach 1 0 min
*Hopewell Rocks 2.5 hours
neighborhood_overview: Maces Bay is an old fishing village, with beautiful coastal views. The area is safe and quiet. There is a small gas station within 2km, and a larger Irving Grab & Go Convenience + NB Liquor, located 3.2km away. Myrtle's Pizza is a local favorite for take out and eat on the cottage deck, or head to the Bay Breeze in Pocologan for east coast fare on their ocean front patio in a casual setting. Head down the street at low tide to a family & dog friendly beach to search for sea glass, sand dollars and hermit crabs.  The basin peninsula is a great place for a short walk, or to launch sea kayaks, and bird watch. Bald eagles nest annually on the islands, and often fly over head.
host_about:
Hi! We are Tracy and John O’Neill.

John is a Caper, and Tracy grew up in a military family, frequently moving. We are both retired military, spending much of our careers on the east coast.
We have 3 children, and our youngest is about to leave the nest. 
We're passionate about animals, especially dogs, and travelling. 
We strive to make Baywatch cottage the epitome of the east coast lifestyle.  Slow, uninterrupted, and completely relaxing.

name: Private Lakefront Nordic Spa @Tides Peak
description:
Couples! Retreat to your private forest to enjoy a private Nordic Spa retreat on a quiet lake off the Saint John River.

Includes an outdoor wood fired hot tub and infrared sauna and hammocks for an ultimate detox in all seasons. Connect around a toasty fire. Unwind in the open concept interior, stocked with luxury modern conveniences. Star gaze from your bed under massive skylights. Stay and be still or enjoy the historic local shops and artisans of Gagetown and Hampstead.
neighborhood_overview: This little hamlet is full of road trip worthy finds, apple orchards, mushroom hunts and geo-caching.
host_about:
We moved our family here in 2019 to slow life down and savour time with our growing teens. We enjoy farming and being outside on the water.

neighborhood_overview:
Grande-Digue is a small community next to Shediac, in Kent County. Our community is recognized as a village for holidaymakers. We have beaches (Cassie Cape beach- Chemin De La Côte, beach at the Cap De Cocagne Marina), hiking trails (in Cocagne and Grande-Digue), etc.

There is a general store (RONA Eudore A. Melanson et fils limité) , Home hardware store, farmers market (Les Digues: fruits and vegetables), small grocery store (Cocagne Variety Ltd), and gas stations.

There are many touristic attractions that are close in proximity to our rental. There is the beach of L'Aboiteau (aproximatively 43km) and Parlee beach (22km). There are also other touristic attractions, such as Kouchibouguac National Park (74 km), Magnetic Hill and Zoo (48 km), Butterfly world (48 km), Centanial parc (44 km), Treego (44 km) and more!

name: Campobello Island Cozy Cottage Retreats
description:
Vocational Summer Retreats & Cottage Living

Come Visit Une BelleVue Where Eagles Soar for:

• Personal Relaxation
• Weekend Getaways
• Intimate Getaways
• Romantic Getaways
• Pillow Talks
• Nature's Retreat
• Fresh Air Getaways

Our house, "Une BelleVue", is an 864 sq ft 2 bedroom cozy bungalow resting on an acre of spectacular views of the Atlantic Ocean, on the beautiful Island of Campobello, NB Canada. 15 minutes from Lubec, Maine.

Bookings Available For Quiet Time...
neighborhood_overview:
It's very peaceful here at "Une BelleVue", where the sunrise is a spectacular view from the house.

Most mornings you'll see the eagles and other birds flying over head calling to each other, enjoying the ocean breeze as they soar the skies. You will also see and hear our beautiful small squirrels scurrying around looking for food and woodpeckers pecking at the bark of the trees. Hope you get to see the "Pileated Woodpecker", they are big and beautiful.

If you bring your bikes there are lots of trails and parks to visit.

You can also drive around the Island, where you will have different views of nearby islands and see the ferry coming into Welshpool.

From the backyard or living room you will also see the Grand Manan Ferries in the distance as they sail by, and watch the fishing boats coming in or going out.

Please note...Book in advance for weekend stays as there are No Saturday Bookings
host_about: Just being me, loveable, and easy to talk to...

name: House of Buchanan
description:
Located in the heart of the village of Riverside-Albert, this thoughtfully renovated heritage house is the perfect place to use as a home base for your Bay of Fundy adventures. Easily take in nearby attractions like Fundy National Park, marys point, Cape Enrage, Hopewell Rocks, beaches, trails, and smalltown treats. You might even spot a hummingbird or two while relaxing on the front porch!
 
Enjoy the freedom, comfort, quiet, and privacy of having access to a whole house and backyard.
neighborhood_overview:
Located in a small, rural Village, quiet side street. The house feels very private although there are friendly neighbour's. A cozy front porch, backyard with picnic table, mature trees, bushes and flowers surround the property.

The crooked creek runs through the village, and there is ample opportunity for walking and bicycling around the village. Nearby are so many beaches and hiking, Caledonia Mountain Gorge, Shepody National Wildlife Preserve and Mary's Point, Cape Enrage and the Fundy National Park and village of Alma are a short drive. The world famous Hopewell Rocks are a short drive as well.

There is access to a water fall, backcountry camping and two lookouts, and picnic area walking distance from the house as well as boat launch. Currently there is a weekly market around the corner which features local food, artisans and farm gate opportunities.

name: Romantic Off-Grid Forest Retreat for Two (Coyote)
description:
The Coyote Cabin is 1/5 cabins at our 100% Indigenous owned healing sanctuary. We have cabins, a thermal spa (separate booking), small gift shop and events.

Hike up to your 108 sqft cozy cabin for an offgrid cultural experience (pack light/backpacks recommended). There is no WiFi/plumbing/electricity in the cabins (we provide water/lighting, a kitchenette and an outhouse).

We also have communal bathrooms/showers by the parking lot.
neighborhood_overview:
The Kingston Historic District is a rare example of a rural centre that has existed since the late 18th century. In 2000, Kingston was designated a historic district under the Province of New Brunswick’s Historic Sites Protection Act. The village was settled in 1783 by Loyalists at the conclusion of the American Revolution. The District is recognized for being a rare surviving example of a rural village which has served the spiritual, commercial and educational needs of the surrounding area since the 1780s.

All of the important buildings befitting a community’s social centre are still present. The prominent positions of the church, school and general store are key elements to the Kingston Historic District.
host_about: Bonjour! Hi! Aaniin! My name is Tasha Robitaille and with my partner, Cory Belcourt and our two beautiful girls we've built a magical retreat in the forest! We have, like many others, been through many changes during this global pandemic and couldn't think of anything better than to build a place where people could find freedom in the forest.

name: The Shipbuilder's Summer Kitchen
description: Spacious grounds surround the Summer Kitchen built in the early 1900's as an addition to the adjacent 1812 Shipbuilder's Cottage. The lower level with its original wide plank floors contains a full kitchen, bathroom and laundry room. The upper level offers a bedroom with double bed and separate living area with a pull-out couch that can sleep two. With it's sloped ceilings and a view of the Bay of Fundy, this cozy space will welcome you after a day exploring the beauty of St. Martins and area.
neighborhood_overview: The cottage is located at 170 West Quaco Rd., 5 km from the Village of St. Martins, the harbour, restaurants, cafe, grocery, gas, art and gift shops, tourist information centre, museum and the Sea Caves. The Fundy Trail is 11 km from the village. Within walking distance of the cottage is The Quaco Head Lighthouse (1.3kms), and Brown's beach (1.9kms) - which is as quiet as it is scenic and a rock lover's dream. There is also a coastal trail that connects the two. On calm nights the world's highest tides can be heard washing into shore, carving the red rock coastline to smooth perfection.

name: Mountain Brook Loft
description: Reconnect with nature. This loft style apartment is located in the basement of my home in beautiful Charlo. It has it's private entrance where you can enjoy the space of two split levels. Created in an open space concept, this aztec style space will help you relax after a full day of visiting the area and or practicing your favorite sport.
neighborhood_overview:
The house is located at 2 km door-to-door to well known Eastern Canadian cross-country ski and biathlon facility. During summer, this location is beautiful for hiking and mountain biking.
You can also find Charlo beach at about 5 minutes drive where you will find the beautiful Baie des Chaleurs and the majestic mountain view over looking the Gaspésie.
Farmers market, local bakery and many local restaurants are all within 5-10 minutes drive.
host_about:
Manager of addiction and mental health community services by day, mom of two boys by evenings / weekends. In between, you’ll find me in the mountains, trail running or on a bike !

name: 10 mins from USA/Canada border/King beds/Hot tub
description:
Escape to an enchanting cottage retreat, nestled on the shores of an environmentally protected lake. Immerse yourself in the serene beauty of nature as you soak in the hot tub and gaze out over the tranquil waters. Everything you need for a perfect lakeside getaway!

✅ Swimming, Kayaking
✅ Fishing, Pedal boating
✅ Arcade Pac-Man, Record Player w/ 45’s
✅ Bonfire pit - firewood provided
✅ Outdoor BBQ
✅ Sleeps 6: 2 King, 1 Queen bed
✅ 51 inch Smart Roku TV
✅ Netflix, Amazon
✅ Screened in porch
neighborhood_overview:
Love The Cottage-Lake Escape offers a great outdoor experience, which we hope will create lasting memories. The beautiful scenic drive to St Andrews, New Brunswick, is 25 -30 minutes and offers whale watching, Marine Center, shopping, restaurants, and much more. Only 10 minutes away from Canada’s Chocolate Town, St Stephen NB, and the Canada/USA border. A luxurious stay in the woods on the lake awaits you!

The lakefront offers year-round fishing with small and big mouth bass, pickerel, and trout. In winter, fall, spring, and summer, enjoy the various activities the area has to offer all year round. Our guests love that they can go pedal boating, kayaking, canoeing, swimming, skating, snow shoeing, cross country skiing, walks on the frozen lake, and all weather permitting. Reconnect with family and friends and enjoy being surrounded in nature all year round!
host_about: We are Cassie and Dave, best friends, happily married, proud parents of four adult children and ten grandchildren. We are very happy to share our beautiful cottage with you. Our hope is that we have created a warm and welcoming space for all our guests.  Our main focus is to make your stay enjoyable! We want our cottage to be relaxing and stocked with all the comforts of home with special touches to make your stay memorable.

name: Cheerful Cottage, Short Walk owners PrivateBeach
description:
A lovely escape from the city for a large family or group getaway, in this peaceful fishing village on the Northumberland Strait, which boasts the warmest water in Atlantic Canada. Enjoy the fresh ocean air sipping your morning coffee on the deck.
Private beach is just 2 min drive or 10 minute walk.Plenty of nature to enjoy on the seaside trails, and forested walking and cycling trails. Enjoy fresh seafood, and local micro brewery , watching the sunset from the nearby waterfront restaurant.
neighborhood_overview:
A quiet little Acadian fishing village on the Northumberland Strait, which boasts some of the warmest waters in Atlantic Canada.
A beautiful private beach is just minutes away. Shops in the village include a grocery store, restaurants, ice cream parlour, L'Aboiteau Provincial Park, and forested walking trails and bicycle trails.

name: *NEW* 3 Bedroom Tidal View Cottage #1
description:
Welcome to our well equipped, modern cottage. This property holds an amazing Bay of Fundy view that is always changing and absolutely stunning! The cottage is located in the beautiful Village of Alma, neighbouring community of Fundy National Park.
One of two cottages located on a quiet dead end street providing a great place to relax for the whole family!
neighborhood_overview: Alma is a little bustling village tucked in snuggly  beside Fundy National Park with it's miles of amazing trails and scenic views, just up the road a step is the Waterside Beach and just a little further is the beautiful Cape Enrage lighthouse, and if you listen on foggy or hazy days you can hear the Foghorn  shouting out a stern warning to the boats that still ply these waters. In the other direction, just outside the Park exit is the road that takes you to the newly opened (at this end) Fundy Trail Parkway, with it's amazing views of the Bay. Alma has an active Wharf that can go from totally quiet to totally busy at the drop of the hat, and it's amazing to watch the boats coming and going, and the hustle and bustle of fisherman as they carry out their days duties, but a person must acknowledge that it is an active, working wharf and as such, must be aware of their surroundings at all times while on or near it .  There are multiple places to eat here during the summer, with the pizza
host_about: Hi I'm Ruth, I've been coming to Alma since I was a little girl, but I've only lived here for 34-35 years. I've raised two kids here, and we've all been the richer for it.  I am an Aquarius so it only stands to reason that I had to end up by the water.

name: The Resort (golf, ATV/ snowmobile trails, skiing)
description:
Come and enjoy our beautiful property on the Saint John River in Nackawic, NB. Our “resort” sleeps 4 guests comfortably with a common area great for lounging, games , TV/ movies & a cute kitchenette for snacks. We also offer 4 kayaks, use of a in-ground pool & a hot tub. Steps away from a 9 hole golf course and a 3 minute drive into the town of Nackawic.

The “resort” is also a great location for multiple hiking trails, ATV trails, snowmobiling & skating and 20 minute drive from Crabbe Mountain
neighborhood_overview: Nackawic is a naturalist paradise, it gets its name from Maliseet word meaning “straight” or “not in the direction it seems” alluding to the intersection created when the Nackawic stream meets the Saint John River. The Resort is located just outside the main town centre minutes away from the Trans Canada Highway, in a little cul de sac, with Nackawic Golf Club being a 2 minute walk from The Resort, this is always a good passage to many snowmobile and ATV trails. Nackawic highlights the World’s Largest Axe and Marina Park, inspiring the name for The Big Axe Brewery located just minutes away for a mid-day pint.
host_about: Hi! I’m Deanna. I moved to New Brunswick in 2004, and I’m originally from Bowmanville, Ontario.  I started this Airbnb with my husband, Derrick, after our children graduated. We are officially empty nesters! I love kayaking, snowshoeing, ATVing & hiking. I would be happy to have you as my guests and enjoy these activities!

neighborhood_overview:
St. Louis-de-Kent, New Brunswick, offers a variety of charming attractions for visitors to explore:

• Bouctouche Dune: Experience the natural beauty of the Bouctouche Dune, a unique coastal sand dune that stretches for kilometers along the Acadian Coast. Enjoy hiking trails, boardwalks, and scenic views of the coastline.

• Irving Eco-Centre: Discover the diverse ecosystem of the Irving Eco-Centre through interpretive trails, birdwatching, and educational exhibits. It's a great spot for nature enthusiasts and families alike.

• Kent Museum: Dive into the local history and culture of the Kent region at the Kent Museum. Learn about the area's Acadian roots, heritage industries, and notable historical figures through exhibits and artifacts.

name: Historic Edwardian Carriage House Ample Parking
description: The Gardeners Cottage in Saint Andrews New Brunswick is a place that's both historic and one of a kind.  Listed in the Canadian registry of historical places and designed by the prominent Maxwell Brothers Architects for the Ogilvie wheat baron F.W. Thompson. Part of the carriage house and stables building on the estate, the gardeners cottage was the home to the groomsmen and gardeners. In the shadow of the Algonquin Hotel close to Katy's Cove and walk-able to downtown Saint Andrews by the Sea.

Historic Water Street is a quick jaunt down to the shore.  If you need your morning coffee fix Tim Hortons is just a couple of blocks away.

Hike up to your 108 sqft cozy cabin for an offgrid cultural experience (pack light/backpacks recommended). There is no WiFi/plumbing/electricity in the cabins (we provide water/lighting, a kitchenette and an outhouse).

neighborhood_overview:
The Kingston Historic District is a rare example of a rural centre that has existed since the late 18th century. In 2000, Kingston was designated a historic district under the Province of New Brunswick’s Historic Sites Protection Act. The village was settled in 1783 by Loyalists at the conclusion of the American Revolution. The District is recognized for being a rare surviving example of a rural village which has served the spiritual, commercial and educational needs of the surrounding area since the 1780s.

All of the important buildings befitting a community’s social centre are still present. The prominent positions of the church, school and general store are key elements to the Kingston Historic District.
host_about: Bonjour! Hi! Aaniin! My name is Tasha Robitaille and with my partner, Cory Belcourt and our two beautiful girls we've built a magical retreat in the forest! We have, like many others, been through many changes during this global pandemic and couldn't think of anything better than to build a place where people could find freedom in the forest.

name: Union House
description:
Union House is our family home, as we split our time between two cities. We love the open concept and the kitchen bar where large and little ones can tuck up for a snack or a chat. The living room is like one big pillow (with TV attached). There's a cupboard full of games, art supplies, and books for all ages.

At Union House, we have tried to make it most everything you would need to have a proper staycation. Cozy, bright, and beautiful is why we love it; we think you will too :)
neighborhood_overview:
Centrally located, Union House is a 5 minute walk from downtown shops, the 5 Kings craft restaurant and brewhouse, and the Garcelon indoor public pool (and sauna!).

We are also a 5 minute walk from the Elm Street nature park and Dover Hill park, both offering wonderful hikes in river valleys, with stunning views of the St Croix rapids. There is also a lovely river walk which starts behind Something's Brewing Cafe.

Don't hesitate to ask us for recommendations on hikes, beaches, and restaurants outside of St. Stephen as well. We know all the swimming holes and sand beaches, as well as the best spots for fish and chips. The resort town of St. Andrews by the Sea is a gorgeous 20 minute drive away, as you follow the St. Croix river from St. Stephen out to the Fundy Bay, where St. Andrews is perched on the end of a peninsula.

name: Bois Joli Relax
description:
(Français en bas)

Kick back and relax in this calm, stylish space. This is a 4 season private oasis. You can enjoy the stars on a clear night sky around the fire pit or in the comforting warmth of the spa. The large deck offers plenty of space for your workout session or your grilling skills! The gazebo is a great place to sip your morning coffee or glass of wine. Walking distance to a tranquil beach and conveniently located near the beaches of Parlee (Shediac) and Aboiteau (Cap-Pelé).
neighborhood_overview:
The cottage is an easy 7 minute walk to a beach (accessible for long walks at low tide). A short 2 minute drive takes you to a very quiet and secluded section of Berner beach that you can enjoy anytime of day regardless of the tide. We are conveniently located between Shediac and Cap-Pelé (10 minute drive in each direction) where you can enjoy great restaurants and world-renowned beaches (Parlee and Aboiteau beaches). A grocery store with great food selection, alchool and gas is less than a 2 minute drive from the cottage. ATV trails are close by.

The cottage is located 7 minutes walk from a beach (where you can walk at low tide). A 2-minute drive away you will find a very quiet and secluded section of Berner Beach accessible regardless of the tide. We are located between Shediac and Cap-Pelé (10 minutes' drive in each direction) where you will find good restaurants and the renowned beaches of Parlee and the Aboiteau. A supermarket with good selection of food, alchool drink

name: Dôme 4: Waterfront-HotTub-AC-BBQ-Kitchen-Bathroom
description:
Experience luxury glamping in Flatlands, NB!
Our domes provide a serene adult-only retreat for those seeking relaxation under a starlit sky, surrounded by the stunning scenery of the Restigouche River and mountains. Enjoy heated floors, air conditioning, a kitchen, and a modern shower in our insulated domes. Unwind in your hot tub year-round, and enjoy patio furniture and BBQ grilling in summer.
Please note: Our fixed check-in at 4 PM NB time. Credit cards only; debit cards are not accepted.
neighborhood_overview:
Flatlands is a beautiful old Village with lots of fishing and logging history, it is a very quiet area surrounded by nature and wild life such as eagles, different bird, beavers etc.
We have close relationships with our neighbors. We ask that you respect our neighbor’s privacy and monitor noise levels during the nighttime. Islandview Drive is a small street, with the Island View Church Cottage at one end and the Glamping Domes at the other end. name: Two minutes from everything!
description:
Easily plan your trip with this easily accessible accommodation, complete with a fully equipped kitchen, private laundry facilities, and free parking for 2 cars. Freshly renovated accommodation located in the heart of Caraquet, opposite Foley Beach where you can relax in the sun, walk on the sand, swim, and rent a kayak. Enjoy a bike ride on the famous VéloRoute which passes nearby.

Here, you're truly close to everything!
neighborhood_overview:
Caraquet, Capital of Acadia, where it's good to live.

Let yourself be charmed by the beauties of the sea and its fresh produce that it offers us fishing and tasting, the new infrastructure of the city, its cultural animation and its pride in the French language.

By staging the charms of nature like the waterfront bike path, beaches and terraces with a magnificent view, taking care to maintain a heritage true to its history, having culinary chefs who will make you live authentic experiences, enjoying tasty cafes, warm little shops, artists who transmit and communicate Acadian culture, varied accommodations that will satisfy you, Caraquet really has everything to please.

Discovering the inclusive, diverse, and colorful essence of this city will come back again and again.

Located in a sprawling, mature-growth apple orchard only 25 minutes from Fredericton, the intimate Orchard Bell tent is ideal for individuals seeking to connect with nature and couples craving quality time.

neighborhood_overview:
Retreat from your daily life however you choose with M.Ruth Retreats, located at 30 Orchard Lane in Tay Creek, New Brunswick. On this 5-acre property, you will find 4 bell tents nestled into the wild remnants of a once commercialized apple orchard and surrounded by an additional 80+ acres of mature forest through which the Tay River winds. After a long day spent hiking, swimming, birdwatching, or partaking in any other number of available outdoor activities, you can enjoy a beverage by your private fire pit or turn out the fairy-lights swaying from the trees and tuck yourself into your sinfully comfortable bed.

If you would prefer to socialize with other guests, the shared lodge is only a 5-minute walk away from every tent and offers a communal fire pit, barbecue, games room/library, outdoor seating area, and hot tub (available by July, 2023) in addition to a fully-equipped kitchen, bathroom and dining area. With its pristine sandy beaches and warm waters, it's an ideal spot for swimming, sunbathing, and beachside picnics. Enjoy beach volleyball, build sandcastles, or take a leisurely stroll along the shoreline. The beach also offers amenities like changing rooms, washrooms, and a canteen for your convenience!

The Point-du-Chene Wharf and Restaurants: Located near Parlee Beach, within a 5-minute walking distance the Wharf is a charming waterfront area bustling with activity. Explore a variety of local restaurants that serve up delicious seafood dishes, from freshly caught lobster and oysters to mouthwatering fish and chips. Enjoy picturesque views of the marina as you savour your meal. As one of the largest and most popular saltwater beaches in Eastern Canada, Parlee Beach provides the perfect backdrop for a fun-filled day with family and friends.

Embrace the maritime culture of Shediac by visiting the Pointe-du-Chêne wharf, where you can immerse yourself in the charming atmosphere of a vibrant fishing village. A PEACEFUL COUNTRY GETAWAY ON A WORKING GOAT FARM.

While we do our absolute best to keep as many of these away from our property as possible, nature rules in the countryside.
host_about: We both come from human service councillor backgrounds. We love homesteading and growing our own food and are excited to share our farm life with our guests!

name: Riverside Basement Suite
description: This little slice of paradise is nestled at the end of a private lane. My bright and airy basement suite has its own private entrance, with self-check-in ability.  This open concept living area has various amenities including hotplate, fridge, air fryer, 55" tv with premium cable and Firestick along with reliable internet. The breathtaking views of the river can be enjoyed from the large yard. We are very close to the tracks and so trains do go by 3 or 4 times a day. Pets are welcome!
neighborhood_overview: I'm at the end of a private lane, just off the Nerepis Road. There is a church across the street and an elementary school a few yards away, It is private and quiet here on the river. There are ducks that live on the river and even the occasional eagle. In the summer the river is a buzz with boats and there are 5 or 6 that moor close to my place. Also a 5 minute walk from the Westfield Ferry that takes you over to the Kingston Peninsula. It is possible to get down to the beach from my property but it's better suited to goats and dogs! Last summer the water was high so there was not much beach at all. There is a convenience store and eatery a 5 minute walk from here, or  Tim Hortons about a 10 minute drive in the heart of Grandbay. I am 20 minutes from Saint John, and 50 minutes from Fredericton. Conveniently located close to hiway access my place is easy to find.
host_about:
This old house is the love of my life! 

Sharing it with people who can appreciate the location right on the river makes me very happy.

 In the summer you will find me puttering in the yard,  looking for the occasional wayward feline, or picking up after 120lb Archie.

Cumberland Bay is a small community, centrally located between three major New Brunswick cities (Fredericton, Moncton, and Saint John).  It has it's own volunteer Fire Department, churches, and a small public wharf nearby (The Range Wharf).

neighborhood_overview:
Cumberland Bay is a small community, centrally located between three major New Brunswick cities (Fredericton, Moncton, and Saint John).  It has it's own volunteer Fire Department, churches, and a small public wharf nearby (The Range Wharf).

The nearby communities of Young's Cove, Waterborough, and Chipman are all within a 10 to 15 minute drive.  You'll find churches, convenience stores, gas bars, take-outs, local markets, public swimming location, marina, and boat launch.  In your vacation rental, there is a Welcome Binder with detailed information about these places.

name: Chalet de bord de mer
neighborhood_overview: Available 4 seasons. Located on the edge of the famous Baie des Chaleurs, the Acadian town of Beresford (Belle Baie) offers a way of life connected with nature. Sunrises over the sea, beach walks, beating, local fauna, and local flora are all attractions of this small locality. The salt marsh interpretation center of the Baie des Chaleur and the municipal beach are a must-see for those who want to get to know the area better. Several activities are offered in summer: yoga, oversized bike rental, kayaks and paddle boards. Close to the town of Bathurst, you can drive there in a few minutes. Bathurst and surrounding towns including Nigadoo and Petit Rocher among others, have several grocery stores, pharmacies, and everything you'll need. Also, several cream shops,  restaurants with a varied menu and charming shops. Seafood and seafood are part of our menu every time you stay.
host_about: Nous sommes deux soeurs, Marielle et Lise, Co-propriétaires de ce lieu de rêve. Il a été construit par nos parents lorsque nous étions toutes mini et nous venons de le prendre en charge. Lise et moi sommes des artistes et des passionnées de jardinage. On a un amour commun pour la couleur.  Nous adorons les baignades matinales dans la Baie des Chaleurs ravigotante, le poisson et les fruits de mer!

Enjoy!

name: Sunset valley, where the stars shine brighter.
description:
Relax with the whole family in this spacious 2 Bedroom basement apartment in an owner occupied dwelling . The apartment has its own entrance . The home is located in a beautiful country setting , minutes from the Nerepis River . It’s a great place for kayakers with lots of hiking trails near by . We are located 30 minutes from Saint John City centre and approx. 40 minutes to Oromocto NB.
We do not charge a cleaning fee , so there is no unexpected cost to you .
neighborhood_overview:
Sunset valley is beautiful are protected by the nature conservatory of Canada .

These two parcels expand NCC’s nature reserve to 319 hectares (787 acres). An adjacent wetland is owned and managed for conservation by Ducks Unlimited Canada.

Small streams cross these properties near the confluence of the Nerepis and Wolastoq/Saint John rivers. The forested property has some trees that are well over 100 years old and is a mixture of white pine, red and black spruce, balsam fir, cedar and black and white ash trees. The Committee on the Status of Endangered Wildlife in Canada has assessed black ash as a threatened species because of impacts from the invasive emerald ash borer.

The lands were entrusted to NCC by Joseph O’Donnell of Fredericton, NB, in honour of his family.

The Sunset Valley Nature Reserve features a trail used by the local community for hiking. This conservation area is important for waterfowl and other wetland birds as well as tw
host_about: My husband and I are both in the healthcare field. We have raised 6 children . We were previously super hosts and had an Airbnb in Saint John which we sold to move to the country . We have just built our retirement home and have decided to re host . Although we haven’t had a lot of time for travelling in the past we are looking forward to exploring as we get close to retirement .

neighborhood_overview:
Parlee Beach: Located within a 5-minute walking distance, Parlee Beach is a must-visit destination. With its pristine sandy beaches and warm waters, it's an ideal spot for swimming, sunbathing, and beachside picnics. Enjoy beach volleyball, build sandcastles, or take a leisurely stroll along the shoreline. The beach also offers amenities like changing rooms, washrooms, and a canteen for your convenience!

The Point-du-Chene Wharf and Restaurants: Located near Parlee Beach, within a 5-minute walking distance the Wharf is a charming waterfront area bustling with activity. Explore a variety of local restaurants that serve up delicious seafood dishes, from freshly caught lobster and oysters to mouthwatering fish and chips. Enjoy picturesque views of the marina as you savour your meal. name: Ocean Views in a Central Location
description: You will be close to everything when you stay in this centrally located home, with a view of the Atlantic Ocean's Bay of Fundy and the Partridge Island lighthouse, located just two blocks from Bayshore Beach, a block from the Carleton Martello Tower national historic landmark and a short jaunt to both Reversing Falls and Saint John's famous Uptown.  With a mix of vintage and whimsical appointments, experience all-new appliances and fixtures in this colourful and incredible place.
neighborhood_overview: Bayshore began being developed in the 1870s and continued through the 1940s.  'Our neighbourhood faces the ocean, is abutted by a small fortress from the War of 1812, and is skirted by a freight line railway, whose trains chug through occasionally and which features a pathway that stretches from just above Bayshore Beach to McLaren's Beach, along bountiful flora and incredible rock formations.   Further down the street is a small graveyard whose earliest interments go back to the 1800s.  On the far reaches of the neighbourhood are the remains of Fort Dufferin.   The area is often foggy and can be quite windy due to its proximity to the ocean, but is nonetheless beautiful - especially on starry nights where you can see almost forever.

Jen
